.TH facial_training 1 "November 2025" "pam_facial_auth 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
facial_training \- train a facial recognition model for a user
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B facial_training
\-u USER \-m METHOD
[\-i DIR] [\-o FILE] [\-f] [\-v]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B facial_training
utility creates or updates a facial recognition model for a user based
on previously captured images.

Supported recognition methods:
.IP \(bu 4
LBPH (Local Binary Pattern Histogram)
.IP \(bu
Eigenfaces
.IP \(bu
Fisherfaces

All images are normalized to 200x200 grayscale frames for consistent
model training.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-u " " USER ", " \-\-user=USER
User whose model is to be trained.
.TP
.BR \-m " " METHOD ", " \-\-method=METHOD
Recognition method: \fBlbph\fR, \fBeigen\fR, or \fBfisher\fR.
.TP
.BR \-i " " DIR ", " \-\-input=DIR
Specify a different base directory for images.
.TP
.BR \-o " " FILE ", " \-\-output=FILE
Specify output path for the model XML file.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Force model overwrite.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable debug mode.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/security/pam_facial.conf
Configuration file used for default settings.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR facial_capture (1),
.BR facial_test (1),
.BR pam_facial_auth (8)
